    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and
        Related Components - Installation - Water Outlet Tube, and Thermostat
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Water Outlet Tube, and Thermostat</title>
        <figure id="f3350012336" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK05/K05007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Water outlet tube and thermostat</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water outlet tube (typical)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If equipped with a thermostat bypass, install a new thermostat seal and then install the
                thermostat bypass housing on the cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install thermostat assembly in the cylinder head or thermostat bypass.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Water outlet tube configurations use either two M8 x 25 bolts to hold the water outlet tube to the
                    cylinder head or two M8 x 115 bolts to hold the water outlet tube and thermostat bypass housing to
                    the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install water outlet tube and finger tighten two M8 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two M8 bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
